classes.name: Collection
classes.description: An utility data structure used within the Discordoo.

construct.name: constructor
construct.description: The Collection() constructor creates {@link Collection} objects.

props.name: empty
props.description: Checks if the collection is empty or not.

props.name: size
props.description: Gets the amount of elements in this collection.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Removes all elements from the collection.

methods.name: clone
methods.description: Creates a new collection based on this one.

methods.name: concat
methods.description: Merges the specified collections into one and returns a new collection.

methods.name: delete
methods.description: Removes element from the collection.

methods.name: equal
methods.description: Checks if two collections are equal.

methods.name: every
methods.description: Checks if all values satisfy the condition.

methods.name: filter
methods.description: Filters out the elements which don't meet requirements and returns array (default).

methods.name: find
methods.description: Searches for the element in collection and returns it.

methods.name: findKey
methods.description: Searches for the key in collection and returns it.

methods.name: first
methods.description: Returns first collection value if it exists.

methods.name: firstKey
methods.description: Returns first collection key if it exists.

methods.name: forEach
methods.description: Executes a function on each of elements of collection.

methods.name: get
methods.description: Gets element from collection.

methods.name: has
methods.description: Checks if an element exists in the collection.

methods.name: intoChunks
methods.description: Returns a collection chunked into several collections.

methods.name: last
methods.description: Returns last collection value if it exists.

methods.name: lastKey
methods.description: Returns last collection key if it exists.

methods.name: map
methods.description: Maps each item to another value into an array.

methods.name: random
methods.description: Gets a random value from collection.

methods.name: reduce
methods.description: Executes a predicate function on each element of the collection, resulting in a single output value.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Sets a new element in the collection.

methods.name: some
methods.description: Checks if any of values satisfies the condition.

props.name: return
props.description: The filter returns array by default, but you can specify what to return using this option

props.name: returnType
props.description:
Random returns only value(s) by default,
but you can specify what to return using this option

props.name: unique
props.description:
Random returns non-unique elements by default,
but you can request unique elements using this option.
Please note that this reduces performance.
